rent evaluation components (exams, assignments, projects).\n- Bars are color-coded according to course themes (Sciences, Humanities, etc.).\n- Include hover-over features for grade details and course descriptions.\n\n### Example Walkthrough:\nImagine a viewer clicking on the third semester in the timeline. The stacked bar chart pops up, showing five bars, each representing a course. The viewer sees that in "Biology 101", 50% of the grade came from exams (colored red in the stack), 30% from lab work (colored green), and 20% from assignments (colored blue). Hovering over these bars could reveal the exact grades (like A, B, etc.) and additional details. In this way, the student can reminisce and evaluate their academic journey, or an advisor can understand the student's academic strengths and areas for improvement.	2024-01-29 03:39:02.067201	2024-01-29 03:39:02.067201
